something relatively simple, that allows me to write in Markdown format, to
replace &lt;a href=&quot;http://carlgay.wordpress.com&quot;&gt;my old blog&lt;/a&gt;, where I also didn’t write
very much.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let’s see if Jekyll knows how to highlight Dylan code…&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-dylan&quot; data-lang=&quot;dylan&quot;&gt;define method fib ()
  let a = 0;
  let b = 1;
  method ()
    let r = a + b;
    a := b;
    b := r;
    a
  end
end;

let f = fib();
for (i from 1 to 20) format-out(&quot;%= &quot;, f()) end&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;</content><author><name></name></author><category term="news" /><summary type="html">This is my new blog, backed by the Jekyll static website generator. I wanted something relatively simple, that allows me to write in Markdown format, to replace my old blog, where I also didn’t write very much.</summary></entry></feed>